The issue with the original code is that it is using the `mkdir()` method, which creates a directory only if it does not already exist. However, if the directory does not exist, it will throw a `FileNotFoundException`. To fix this, you can use the `mkdirs()` method instead, which creates the directory and any missing parent directories.

Here is the updated code using `mkdirs()` method:
```java
public void makeDirectory(String path, String nameFolder) {
    File dir = new File(path + "\\" + nameFolder);
    dir.mkdirs();
}
```
With this change, the directory will be created even if it does not exist, and no `FileNotFoundException` will be thrown.
